(SECTION 1: COMMERCIAL REAL ESTATE LOAN POLICY) Tj
0 -20 Td /F1 10 Tf
(1.1 Loan-to-Value Ratios) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The maximum Loan-to-Value LTV ratio for Commercial Real Estate CRE loans) Tj
0 -15 Td
(is 75 percent for standard income-producing properties. Special-use properties) Tj
0 -15 Td
(such as churches gas stations and car washes are capped at 65 percent LTV.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Senior Loan Officers may approve exceptions up to 80 percent LTV provided that) Tj
0 -15 Td
(the Debt Service Coverage Ratio DSCR exceeds 1.35 and a Credit Manager) Tj
0 -15 Td
(counter-signs the approval memo within 24 hours.) Tj
0 -30 Td /F1 12 Tf
(1.2 Debt Service Coverage Ratio Requirements) Tj
0 -20 Td /F1 10 Tf
(Minimum DSCR for CRE loans is 1.25 at origination. Loans with DSCR below) Tj
0 -15 Td
(1.20 require Risk Officer approval and must be classified as Watch List.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Quarterly DSCR monitoring is mandatory for all CRE loans above 2 million dollars.) Tj
0 -30 Td /F1 12 Tf
(SECTION 2: RESIDENTIAL MORTGAGE UNDERWRITING STANDARDS) Tj
0 -20 Td /F1 10 Tf
(2.1 Credit Score Requirements) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Minimum credit score for conforming residential mortgages is 680. Jumbo loans) Tj
0 -15 Td
(defined as loans exceeding 726200 dollars require a minimum credit score of 720.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(FHA-insured loans may be approved with scores as low as 580 with 3.5 percent) Tj
0 -15 Td
(down payment or 500 with 10 percent down payment.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(2.2 Debt-to-Income Ratio Limits) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Front-end DTI housing expenses must not exceed 28 percent of gross monthly) Tj
0 -15 Td
(income. Back-end DTI all monthly debt obligations must not exceed 43 percent) Tj
0 -15 Td
(for Qualified Mortgages as defined under CFPB Regulation Z.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Non-QM products may allow back-end DTI up to 50 percent with compensating) Tj
0 -15 Td
(factors including 12 months cash reserves and credit score above 740.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(2.3 Documentation Requirements) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Full documentation required: W-2 forms for past 2 years tax returns for past) Tj
0 -15 Td
(2 years 3 months bank statements pay stubs for 30 days and full appraisal) Tj
0 -15 Td
(by an approved panel appraiser. Self-employed borrowers must provide) Tj
0 -15 Td
(24 months of business and personal tax returns plus CPA-prepared P&L statement.) Tj
0 -30 Td /F1 12 Tf
(SECTION 3: BSA/AML COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENTS) Tj
0 -20 Td /F1 10 Tf
(3.1 Mandatory Training) Tj
0 -15 Td
(All staff must complete BSA/AML training annually. New employees must complete) Tj
0 -15 Td
(training within 30 days of hire. Completion is tracked in the LMS system.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Failure to complete training within the deadline results in system access suspension.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(3.2 Suspicious Activity Reports) Tj
0 -15 Td
(SARs must be filed within 30 calendar days of detecting suspicious activity.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Transactions over 10000 dollars in cash require Currency Transaction Reports CTRs.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(All SAR filings must be reviewed by the Chief Compliance Officer CCO before) Tj
0 -15 Td
(submission. Violations must be reported to CCO within 48 hours of discovery.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(3.3 OFAC Screening) Tj
0 -15 Td
(All customers and transactions must be screened against the OFAC SDN list.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(International wire transfers require dual OFAC screening and BSA Officer approval.) Tj
0 -30 Td /F1 12 Tf
